<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-10-29T06:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-10-29T06:00:00-05:00" n="470" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d470">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/12495: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Shanghai (<persName type="from">Cunningham</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-10-29T19:00:00+08:00">October 29, 1933—7
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received October 29—6:45 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>T. V. Soong has presented his resignation as Minister of Finance which
                            has been accepted, H. H. Kung has been appointed as successor. Soong
                            will continue to be connected with the National Economic Council.</p>
                        <p>Repeated to Department.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Cunningham</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>